node.text:
caelynn and i are raising money to donate to wetheprotesters and @campaignzero to take a stand against racism and police brutality. we can live in a world where the police don't kill people by limiting police interventions, improving community interactions, and ensuring accountability.

we also want to go camping with those of you who have the desire to help! by donating at the link in our bio, you and your friends are automatically entered to win a camping trip with us. screenshot your donation and dm them to us for a chance to win.

our goal is to raise $50,000. we kicked off the donations with one of our own and, if we reach our goal, i’ve agreed to let @caelynnmillerkeyes shave my head. so let’s make it happen!

node.text:
santorini nights ✨

another imperfect time lapse but i spent way too much time working on this one not to post 😅 i set the camera up right outside of our room in oía. the light from the restaurants/houses meant i couldn’t set the shutter for too long otherwise the city is blown out but that means the stars are less vibrant. with that in mind, i set the interval to every 3 seconds. little did i realize at the time that would mean way more photos over the same amount of time that would lead to way more processing. i set the camera up and went to sleep. i woke up in the morning, not to my surprise, to a full memory card. once i started piecing it all together i realized i had 2,000 raw images to process and throw into a video. after all the work my poor laptop had to do, i realized my camera somehow missed like 500 photos somewhere in the middle? not sure how or why but i’ve exhausted my search efforts and this is the best i can do, much to my own chagrin.

i can’t remember the exact settings (nor do i have the know-how to find them after the fact) but it was something along the lines of 20mm, 3” shutter, f1.8, ISO 3200

always grateful for the learning experiences!

node.text:
leaving the van behind for a few weeks while caelynn and i go explore some place new.

the perks of getting stuck in the mud, astro shots! one of the few clear nights i had over the last months due to raging wildfires out west. hoping for cooler temps and a whole bunch of rain to help offset this crazy hot summer we’ve been having.
